oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Program of the America First
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A multi page program for "BOYS OF COMPANY 'A' MACHINE BATTALION" that contains a history of the unit, a full page ad for Ford motor cars, and a memorial list of unit members killed during World War I. This copy belonged to the Ring family of Franklin, TN. Pvt. Frank M. Ring, Co. A, 114th MG Battn., 30th Div. was killed in action in October 1918.
